eNCA reporter Tshegohaco Moagi is at the Grasmere tollgate in Johannesburg now. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police, the army, and in some cases private security, are enforcing the lockdown. Authorities have warned they are not tolerating flimsy excuses for being on the road. READ: Denel to produce ventilators in coronavirus fight Several people have been arrested since Friday for breaking the rules. 1885 people are infected and nine have died across the country. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. Several taxis have been impounded for overloading and operating outside the stipulated hours in Freedom Park, Johannesburg. Courtesy #DStv403